                            <comment id="15490293" author="sergey-b" created="Wed, 14 Sep 2016 12:18:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is my pom.xml and possible patch (not tested).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15492792" author="cziegeler" created="Thu, 15 Sep 2016 08:56:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting, I&apos;ve committed a potential fix, could you please give this a try?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15493339" author="sergey-b" created="Thu, 15 Sep 2016 13:37:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nothing has changed. Please, note that properties file format allows only ISO8859-1 encoding. &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/Properties.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/Properties.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue was not in that encoding is platform-dependent, but that it was other than ISO8859-1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If one uses method store(OutputStream), class Properties makes character escaping. When the method store(Writer) it is the responsibility of user.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15493436" author="cziegeler" created="Thu, 15 Sep 2016 14:15:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good point, I&apos;ve changed the code accordingly&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15493594" author="sergey-b" created="Thu, 15 Sep 2016 15:09:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Now the problem is fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
